article.description: — Thomas Bell had 14 points as North Texas defeated Sam Houston 65-55 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Bell leads North Texas over Sam Houston St. 65-55
article.linkText: Bell leads North Texas over Sam Houston St. 65-55
article.story: DENTON, Texas -- — Thomas Bell had 14 points as North Texas defeated Sam Houston 65-55 on Tuesday night. Abou Ousmane had 13 points for North Texas (6-3), which won its fourth consecutive game. Mardrez McBride added 12 points. Tylor Perry had 10 points. Savion Flagg had 20 points for the Bearkats (3-7). Jaden Ray added 10 points.
